@Node Main "Readme.guide"



                             TRASHMASTER V1.5

              The *ultimate* in byte disposal for the Amiga.

          Copyright (C) 1993 By Aric R Caley and Greywire designs

                               31 July 1993

   In short, this a "super trashcan" that deletes icons dropped into it, as
opposed to the normal trashcan that is simply a directory on the disk.
And, unlike some other similar programs, Trashmaster makes sure Workbench
properly removes its icons..even if they are icons that Workbench made on
the fly with the `Show  » All Files' option.

   There are other programs out there, that do exactly the same things.  I
don't think any of us have copied from each other, we just all had the same
basic idea.  However, Trashmaster is much better than anything I've yet
seen - its smaller (no big deal, though), and it handles things better.
For instance, none of them seem to properly delete files if the icon is a
"fake" icon created by the Workbench `Show » All Files' option (the icon
never goes away).


